# The 2026 Iran War: Ten Predictive Intelligence Gaps Filled

The Iran-US war, now in its 47th day, has entered a decisive inflection window. A fragile ceasefire expires around April 21-22, the War Powers Resolution 60-day clock hits on April 29-May 1, and the US naval blockade of Iranian ports became operational on April 13. The next two weeks will determine whether this conflict resolves through exhaustion or escalates into something qualitatively worse. This report fills ten specific analytical gaps left by earlier coverage, with every finding oriented toward what happens next.

